<p>In generated wsdl file (form WCF service) there is a strange name template (maybe only for me). For example section describing a method:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;wsdl:message name="InterfaceName_MethodName_InputMessage"&gt;     &lt;wsdl:part name="parameters" element="tns:MethodName"/&gt; &lt;/wsdl:message&gt; </code></pre>  <p>How can i force WCF not to generate <em>InterfaceName</em> prefix and <em>InputMessage</em> postfix? The same situation is in <em>OutputMessage</em> case. I want wsdl to look as shown below:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;wsdl:message name="MethodName"&gt;     &lt;wsdl:part name="parameters" element="tns:MethodName"/&gt; &lt;/wsdl:message&gt; </code></pre>